    <body class="- topic/body " xtrc="body:1;21:11" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita">
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:1;22:12" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita"> ECOMAPP is a normalized, SKU-driven data model with centralized pricing logic and strong
            referential integrity. The catalog supports 4,824 sellable SKUs derived from 104 base
            product types and 63 style modifiers, designed to be scalable and consistent with
            updates.</p>
        <image class="- topic/image " href="../../../../../../../Downloads/322.drawio.png" id="image_ugv_53r_q3c" placement="inline" xtrc="image:1;26:93" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita"/>
        <section class="- topic/section " id="section_tsz_szw_q3c" xtrc="section:1;27:43" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrc="title:2;28:20" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita">ECOMAPP database components</title>
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:2;29:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita">The ECOMDB01 database is organized into 15 tablespaces, with each table placed in its
                own space to support flexibility and management. It includes the USERS, TOKENS,
                SERIES, STYLES, STYLE_MODIFIERS, PRODUCT_TYPES, PRODUCT_VARIANTS, VARIANT_IMAGES,
                INVENTORY, CARTS, CART_ITEMS, ADDRESSES, ORDERS, ORDER_ADDRESSES, and ORDER_ITEMS
                tables, covering the core data structures of the system. Indexing is handled through
                primary key indexes along with business key indexes to maintain efficient and
                reliable query performance.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="- topic/section " id="section_mgk_4rd_q3c" xtrc="section:2;37:43" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrc="title:3;38:20" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita">Normalization</title>
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:3;39:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/jheckel/Documents/Repositories/Spectre/Spectre/docs/Database-Documentation/topics/database-administrator-guide-topic.dita">ECOMAPP NXTCG demonstrates a high level of normalization, with the schema aligning
                with Third Normal Form (3NF). All relations satisfy the requirements of First and
                Second Normal Forms, and the use of composite‑key tables ensures that each non‑key
                attribute is fully dependent on the entire primary key.</p>
        </section>
